This paper deals with techniques for efficiently studying a large corpus of documents, which is a common problem in information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP). The paper also mentions the use of machine learning algorithms, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of datasets generated from existing literature reviews, which could fall under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Overall, the most likely categories are information retrieval (cs.IR), computational linguistics (cs.CL), and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI), with data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) being a less likely but still possible category.
